<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,324,1529,1555]" box="[189,324,1529,1555]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1529,1555]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1529,1555]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[189,1399,1575,1672]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
The name is considered as an adjective derived from the geographical name ‘Taita’ referring to the 
<collectingRegion box="[189,247,1611,1637]" country="Kenya" name="Taita/Taveta" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Taita</collectingRegion>
Hills, located in southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[599,679,1611,1637]" name="Kenya" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Kenya</collectingCountry>
. The 
<collectingRegion box="[740,798,1611,1637]" country="Kenya" name="Taita/Taveta" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Taita</collectingRegion>
Hills are the northernmost block of the Eastern Arc Mountain chain.
</paragraph>
