<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,303,491,517]" box="[189,303,491,517]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,491,517]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,491,517]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1399,537,1162]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Meyer &amp; Copeland" authorityYear="2009" box="[189,407,537,564]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="whartoni">
<emphasis box="[189,407,537,564]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ceratitis whartoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="De Meyer M. &amp; Copeland R." box="[629,988,537,564]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="21 - 26" refId="ref9944" refString="De Meyer M. &amp; Copeland R. 2009. A new Ceratitis from Kenya (Diptera: Tephritidae). Journal of Afrotropical Zoology 5: 21 - 26." type="journal article" year="2009">De Meyer &amp; Copeland (2009)</bibRefCitation>
from forested areas in the Central Highlands of 
<collectingCountry box="[350,427,573,599]" name="Kenya" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Kenya</collectingCountry>
(Gatamayu Forest, Nyanduma Forest, Mt. 
<collectingCountry box="[937,1014,573,599]" name="Kenya" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Kenya</collectingCountry>
Forest), all reared from fruits of 
<taxonomicName box="[189,474,608,634]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" genus="Lepidotrichilia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="volkensii">
<emphasis box="[189,474,608,634]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Lepidotrichilia volkensii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[488,616,608,635]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Meliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Meliaceae</taxonomicName>
). It was an enigmatic species because of the dimorphic wing pattern, with that of the male largely differing from the standard wing banding found in most other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MacLeay" authorityYear="1829" box="[1296,1399,643,669]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1296,1399,643,669]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ceratitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. A series of specimens reared from the same host plant collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[1044,1102,678,704]" country="Kenya" name="Taita/Taveta" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Taita</collectingRegion>
Hills (approximately 
<quantity metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="km" value="400.0">400 km</quantity>
southeast of the nearest site of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Meyer &amp; Copeland" authorityYear="2009" box="[603,744,713,740]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="whartoni">
<emphasis box="[603,744,713,740]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. whartoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are morphologically almost identical, with only slight differences in wing pattern and female aculeus (male wing with dark marking in cell dm occupying more than half of cell in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Meyer &amp; Copeland" authorityYear="2009" box="[421,563,784,810]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="whartoni">
<emphasis box="[421,563,784,810]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. whartoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, less than half in 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyer &amp; Mwatawala &amp; Copeland &amp; Virgilio, 2016" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Mwatawala &amp; Copeland &amp; Virgilio" authorityYear="2016" box="[779,927,784,810]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taitaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[779,927,784,810]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. taitaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[936,1032,784,810]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; female wing with discal band complete in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Meyer &amp; Copeland" authorityYear="2009" box="[331,470,819,845]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="whartoni">
<emphasis box="[331,470,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. whartoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, partially interrupted in cell dm in 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyer &amp; Mwatawala &amp; Copeland &amp; Virgilio, 2016" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Mwatawala &amp; Copeland &amp; Virgilio" authorityYear="2016" box="[872,1017,819,845]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taitaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[872,1017,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. taitaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1024,1116,820,846]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; aculeus with bifurcated apex more slender in 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyer &amp; Mwatawala &amp; Copeland &amp; Virgilio, 2016" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Mwatawala &amp; Copeland &amp; Virgilio" authorityYear="2016" box="[450,598,855,881]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taitaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[450,598,855,881]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. taitaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[608,701,855,881]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(less than one-third of entire width) and invagination less deep than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Meyer &amp; Copeland" authorityYear="2009" box="[335,474,889,916]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="whartoni">
<emphasis box="[335,474,889,916]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. whartoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, the analysis of the available DNA barcodes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Meyer &amp; Copeland" authorityYear="2009" box="[1151,1289,889,916]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="whartoni">
<emphasis box="[1151,1289,889,916]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. whartoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[1305,1391,889,916]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="3.[187,256,541,569]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Table 1. Accessionnumbers and details of the reference DNAbarcodes deposited in the Barcodeof Life Data Systems(BOLD, http://www.boldsystems. org). PT = paratype; SP = non-type (supplementary) material; F = female; M = male. Negative latitudes are S. Longitudes are E." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/46F56602FFF1AB290DC99A79F97BFDB3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" tableUuid="46F56602FFF1AB290DC99A79F97BFDB3">Table 1</tableCitation>
; Supplementary file) revealed remarkable genetic differentiation from 
<taxonomicName authority="Meyer &amp; Mwatawala &amp; Copeland &amp; Virgilio, 2016" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Mwatawala &amp; Copeland &amp; Virgilio" authorityYear="2016" box="[1012,1160,925,951]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taitaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1012,1160,925,951]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. taitaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1169,1260,925,951]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(p-distance = 8.5%). It was, therefore, decided to recognize this as a separate species. The 
<collectingRegion box="[1135,1193,960,986]" country="Kenya" name="Taita/Taveta" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Taita</collectingRegion>
Hills are a chain of forested mountain tops surrounded by the flat and dry Tsavo Plains. They form the northernmost mountainous massif of the Eastern Arc Mountains, a chain of ancient crystalline mountains (
<bibRefCitation author="Burgess N. D. &amp; Butynski T. M. &amp; Cordeiro N. J. &amp; Doggart N. H. &amp; Fjeldsa J. &amp; Howell K. M. &amp; Kilahama F. B. &amp; Loader S. P. &amp; Lovett J. C. &amp; Mblinyi B. &amp; Menegon M. &amp; Moyer D. C. &amp; Nashanda E. &amp; Perkin A. &amp; Rovero F. &amp; Stanley W. T. &amp; Stuart S. N." pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="209 - 231" refId="ref9495" refString="Burgess N. D., Butynski T. M., Cordeiro N. J., Doggart N. H., Fjeldsa J., Howell K. M., Kilahama F. B., Loader S. P., Lovett J. C., Mblinyi B., Menegon M., Moyer D. C., Nashanda E., Perkin A., Rovero F., Stanley W. T. &amp; Stuart S. N. 2007. The biological importance of th Eastern Arc Mountains of Tanzania and Kenya. Biological Conservation 134: 209 - 231. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. biocon. 2006.08.015" type="journal article" year="2007">
Burgess 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
) and are considered a major biodiversity hotspot (
<bibRefCitation author="De Meyer M." box="[874,1101,1065,1092]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="439 - 467" refId="ref9803" refString="De Meyer M. 2000. Systematic revision of the subgenus Ceratitis MacLeay s. s. (Diptera, Tephritidae). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 128: 439 - 467. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2000. tb 01523. x" type="journal article" year="2000">
Meyers 
<emphasis box="[971,1022,1065,1091]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al</emphasis>
. 2000
</bibRefCitation>
). We place this species in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[349,499,1101,1127]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Ceratalaspis">
<emphasis box="[349,499,1101,1127]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ceratalaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the same reasons as outlined in 
<bibRefCitation author="De Meyer M. &amp; Copeland R." box="[923,1278,1100,1127]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="21 - 26" refId="ref9944" refString="De Meyer M. &amp; Copeland R. 2009. A new Ceratitis from Kenya (Diptera: Tephritidae). Journal of Afrotropical Zoology 5: 21 - 26." type="journal article" year="2009">De Meyer &amp; Copeland (2009)</bibRefCitation>
regarding the placement of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Meyer &amp; Copeland" authorityYear="2009" box="[392,532,1136,1162]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="whartoni">
<emphasis box="[392,532,1136,1162]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C. whartoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
